checklist_comments: First checklist of the big road trip "the Great North". Walking along road while CC in traffic jam!
Looking for Collared Flycatcher in this known breeding site. We ended up doing quite a big loop first through the forest and then back through the fields at dusk.
Started early on my own with the bike and only realised after 1-2hrs that we've been to this place before!!!, looking for a spotted crake.
Stopped from the bike on my return as this section of the forest seemed quite birdy and indeed, a nice list of species for 3 minutes!
Stopped at this known breeding site of Crested Lark.
Fuel fill-up stop.
Visting this place mostly to see Melodious Warbler. Very nice loop with the bike.
Mostly looking for the breeding Barred Warbler. Nice loop with bike around the smaller lake, which still took a long time. A bit of rain on the way back and quite windy!
Night bike tour looking for Nightjar and Woodcock.

Bike loop of the heath in early morning. Nice place with good abundance of cool species such at Wood lark, Wood Warbler, Oriole, Cuckoo, Willow Warbler, Common Redstart, Yellowhammer, but no Tawny pipit!
With the main target found quickly, we enjoyed exploring the up and down of this forest with our bike with some off-piste!
Parked at 53.192093, 14.077562. Quick exploration of the place while AN was coocking. Realised at this point that we came here before for LSEA!

The rain won't stop us! After staying in a single spot on our first visit last time, I thought we had to explore a bit more the inside of the area. Good birds to be found from the path inside, but sadly not a great loop to do. Relatively active despite weather!
Evening stop when the rain was supposed to end (it did not!!) looking for some wader at this quarry. Parked at 53.148492, 14.117697 and walked, most waders found at 53.153046, 14.116416.

Early morning walk on my own through the wet grass to check the smaller pond where Little Crake have been reported. Very high density of Sedge, Reed and Savi's warblers!    GPS stopped working, full circle around the small lake (not super easy to walked), then straight back to the parking
